[2] MOH Uganda: 23 Sep 2022
Date: Fri 23 Sep 2022
Source: Ministry of Health Uganda [edited]
https://mobile.twitter.com/MinofHealthUG


Update on Ebola Outbreak In Mubende District (Uganda)
-----------------------------------------------------
The Ministry of Health would like to update the public on the current status of the Ebola Virus Disease (EVD) Outbreak in Mubende District.

In the last 24 hours, 4 cases of Ebola were confirmed, bringing the cumulative number of confirmed cases to 11. Three new deaths were recorded, bringing the total number of cumulative deaths to 11 (including confirmed and probable deaths). Of these, 8 deaths were from the community whereas 3 are facility based. Currently, there are 25 cases on admission at the health facility, out of which 6 are confirmed while 19 are suspected for EVD. [See updated numbers above. I included these numbers to follow the trajectory. - Mod.LK]

The Ministry of Health Rapid Response Teams remain on ground to list and follow up contacts to the confirmed cases. Cumulatively, a total of 58 contacts have been listed.

The Minister of Health, Dr Jane Ruth Aceng Ocero will hold the National Health Task Force in Mubende Council Hall, tomorrow [24 Sep 2022]. The Ministry of Health wishes to advise the general public to install hand washing facilities at all public facilities.

Note to editor:
Probable case: Any person who died from 'suspected' EVD and had an epidemiological link to a confirmed case but was not tested and did not have laboratory confirmation of the disease

Confirmed case: A suspected case with a positive laboratory result for either virus antigen or to viral RNA detected by RT-PCR for Ebola.

[Contact: Emmanuel Ainebyoona, <Emmanuel.ainebyoona@health.com>]

--
Communicated by:
ProMED Rapporteur Lim Wey Wen

